The article discusses the commemoration of the unification of Italy as a single state and the establishment of United States-Italy diplomatic relations. It highlights the strong friendship between the two nations, particularly for Americans of Italian ancestry. The article emphasizes the commitment to mutual prosperity, security, and democratic values, including human rights. It also mentions the willingness of the United States and Italy to face future challenges together, such as the COVID-19 pandemic, economic recovery, and climate change. The proclamation by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. designates April 13 as a day to celebrate the long-standing partnership between Italy and the United States and encourages Americans to honor this enduring friendship.